"'''To Fight Another Day'''" was a short story written by [[Kathy Tyers]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 6|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 6]] by [[West End Games]] in [[May]] [[1995]] and was later archived online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
[[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]], fugitive from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]], arrives at [[Silver Station]] to hand over her prototype portable [[Deflector shield/Legends|shielding]] technology to a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] contact, the elderly [[Una Poot]]. Tinian meets the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Chenlambec]] and asks to be apprenticed to him. She departs with the Wookiee aboard his [[Starship/Legends|starship]], [[Wroshyr (starship)|''Wroshyr'']]. Around the same time, Rebels carrying the wounded [[Daye Azur-Jamin]] also arrive at Silver Station. His [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] recovery is cut short when he and the Rebels are forced to flee the station as it comes under attack by an [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial'' Star Destroyer]].

==Continuity==
This story took place three [[Standard week/Legends|weeks]] after ''[[Tinian on Trial]]'' ([[1995]]) and featured the first meeting of [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian]] and [[Chenlambec]], who would appear in the short story ''[[The Prize Pelt: The Tale of Bossk]]'' ([[1996]])<ref name="TERC" />

